data.meta_description: Visit the Woodburn, Oregon branch of Oregon State Credit Union, a financial cooperative offering personal, business, investment and insurance services.
data.text:
Oregon State Credit Union in Woodburn, Oregon offers ATM, lobby or phone access at 800-732-0173.

Banking services include loans and savings for personal or business needs; investments and insurance; and community financial education.

Not a member? Join Oregon State Credit Union online today.

The Oregon State Credit Union routing number is: 323274270.

Did you know that the Woodburn branch building was opened in early 2020? Pictured below is branch manager Patrick Schmerber cutting the ribbon at the opening ceremony.

In the Woodburn community

Woodburn branch manager, Patrick Schmerber, is a member of the Woodburn Rotary Club and the Woodburn Area Chamber of Commerce. He regularly volunteers with Woodburn Rotary's "Mud Sweat and BBQ" and the Wooden Shoe Tulip Festival. Patrick speaks Spanish fluently and has volunteered at Fiesta Mexicana, Woodburn's Mexican culture festival.

About the credit union

Oregon State Credit Union is a member-owned, not-for-profit financial cooperative, open to anyone who lives or works in 24 western and central Oregon counties.

Learn more about Oregon State Credit Union and financial services career options at our credit union.
